# PNPM Build

## When to use

- Installing Node.js dependencies with pnpm (instead of npm or yarn)
- Running Vite dev server (`pnpm dev`) or production builds (`pnpm build`)
- Managing frontend assets in Laravel projects with Vite
- Adding or removing npm packages via pnpm (`pnpm add`, `pnpm remove`)
- Setting up Filament custom themes with Vite and pnpm build
- Configuring vite.config.js for Laravel, Tailwind v4, React (Inertia), or Vue (Inertia)
- Setting up Alpine.js with Livewire in a pnpm-managed project
- Configuring pnpm workspaces for monorepo projects (pnpm-workspace.yaml)
- Setting up CI/CD with pnpm in GitHub Actions (pnpm/action-setup, frozen-lockfile)
- Troubleshooting pnpm issues (peer deps, Vite cache, hot reload, build failures)
- Cleaning node_modules and pnpm store (`pnpm store prune`)

